column4: Road Running Shoe RUNlight New York Men
column9: This lightweight men’s running shoe is designed for serious, underpronating to neutral runners who work out or compete on a regular basis, preferably on hard surfaces like tarmac, gravel, or solid soil. For a sock-like fit and maximum comfort, the New York from PRO TOUCH’s RUNlight collection is made of the lightest, yet durable performance materials available. This starts with a synthetic mesh/PU mix of the upper construction, which delivers an incredible light feeling. At the same time the material is soft, breathable, and still stable enough to provide enough foothold around the ankle for a safe run. The low-weight internal Pro Bridge delivers the energy from impact to toe-off to allow a smooth and efficient running style. For a dry feeling under the foot, the anatomically shaped and pre-moulded OrthoLite® insole is breathable, moisture wicking, and anti-microbial. In combination with the lightweight Pro Cushion midsole construction with focus on rear and forefoot cushioning, this lightweight midsole provides superior shock absorption and durability at minimal weight. A non-marking Dura Grip rubber outsole adds cushioning and reliable friction without adding one unnecessary gram to the construction. Available in color: Blue/orange and white/blue

The shoe’s rugged Pro Grip outsole is made of a special rubber compound offering superior grip on every terrain and surface. The Ridge Trail AQM for women is equipped with a Cushion Fit midsole that reliably absorbs shock while being extremely lightweight and offering a maximum of comfort. PRO TOUCH’s extremely easy-to-use Quick Lace System provides an evenly distributed pressure around the entire foot, resulting in a significantly enhanced tight and comfortable fit. To protect you against bad weather, the Ridge Trail features an upper made of light canvas, mesh, and synthetics with an integrated waterproof, windproof, and breathable Aquamax® membrane. This technology does not only keep water out, it also regulates the foot climate and keeps you comfortable and dry inside your shoes at all times. Last, but not least, a well cushioned, anatomically shaped and pre-moulded OrthoLite® insole guarantees additional breathability and avoids odours and bacteria that may develop around the foot during long and intense runs. The Ridge Trail AQM for women is an essential piece of trail running equipment – at a truly competitive price! Available in color: Black/silver/fuchsia

Great comfort and low weight: The OZ Pro for men is a well-cushioned running shoe for neutral-gait runners who are looking for lightweight footwear for longer distances. The design of the shoe is sleek and reduced, but it’s not compromising any of its important performance properties: It features Cushion Fit, which is a midsole construction designed to absorb shock and provide high comfort at a very low weight. The Easy Grip outsole is very abrasion-resistant and offers good and reliable grip. On the inside, a breathable OrthoLite® insole ensures great fit as well as perfect moisture management and an odourless and bacteria-free foot climate. Available in colors: Black/white/red, blue/green/white, blue/orange/black and white/black/blue
Also available in colors: White and Blue

column4: Trail Running Shoe Ridgerunner II M Men
column9: With the Ridgerunner II for men, PRO TOUCH is offering a trail running shoe that will not let you down. With the shock absorbing and lightweight Cushion Fit midsole, the Ridgerunner II is well prepared for the rougher conditions when you run off-road. It is also equipped with a durable Pro Grip trail outsole that ensures great traction in all conditions. The upper is made of tough canvas, breathable mesh, and synthetic to protect your foot and to control the foot climate. Underneath your foot, a pre-moulded I-Shape insole offers stability and additional cushioning. The extremely easy-to-use Quick Lace System provides an evenly distributed pressure around the entire shoe, resulting in a snug and comfortable fit.  Available in colors: Black/blue/orange and black/green/lime

The Velcro version of the Rebel Jr was specifically developed for young athletes looking for a lightweight, stable and comfortable performance shoe. A breathable lightweight upper mesh in conjunction with the PRO TOUCH Wrap technology provides the foot with enhanced motion control and fit. The Control Bridge midfoot support and a lightweight midsole compound enhance shock absorption and stability. In addition the Rebel is equipped with anatomically shaped and pre-moulded EVA I-Shape insoles for improved comfort. To protect the upper from excessive wear the toe area is re-enforced with an abrasion resistant PU material. The non-marking Dura Grip outsole offers good grip and reliable durability for a multitude of different indoor sports.

The Speed Rebel is a high-performance indoor handball shoe that combines minimum weight with excellent comfort and support. To stabilize the foot during extreme lateral movements and quick directional changes, the Speed Rebel is equipped with Stability Wings. In addition the Pro Wrap technology  further re-enforces the shoe and gives the foot for enhanced motion control and stability. The upper consists of tough PU and a lightweight technical mesh to ensure high breathability  and comfort. The pre-shaped OrthoLite® insole is highly breathable, long lasting and anti-microbial. In combination with the lightweight midsole compound, it provides superior cushioning and durability. The ProBridge is a lightweight arch support that provides additional torsional rigidity in the midfoot while retaining the structural integrity of the shoe. The non-marking Pro Grip outsole has premium grip characteristics and a high abrasion resistance.

column4: Trail Running Shoe Ridge Trail AQM Men
column9: PRO TOUCH’s top trail running shoe Ridge Trail AQM for men is fully equipped and designed for serious trail action. The rough Pro Grip outsole is made of a special rubber compound offering superior grip on every terrain and surface. The Ridge Trail AQM was also designed to offer a maximum of comfort, which is realized by integrating a Cushion Fit midsole that reliably absorbs shock while being extremely lightweight. PRO TOUCH’s Quick Lace System provides an evenly distributed pressure around the entire foot, resulting in a significantly improved tight and comfortable fit. Since you should always be prepared for any kind of weather, the Ridge Trail features an upper made of light canvas, mesh, and synthetics with an integrated waterproof, windproof, and breathable Aquamax® membrane. This technology does not only keep the rain out, it also regulates the foot climate and keeps you comfortable and dry inside your shoes at all times. Last, but not least, a well cushioned and pre-moulded OrthoLite® insole guarantees additional breathability and avoids odours and bacteria that may develop around the foot during long and intense runs.

The Ridge Trail AQM for women is an essential piece of trail running equipment – at a truly competitive price!

column4: Road Running Shoe Tokyo Stability II Men
column9: With the Tokyo Stability II for men, PRO TOUCH offers a stable and solid running shoe with great comfort and flex. The breathable shoe is designed for runners with a normal arch, providing a comfortable ride mile after. The innovative and lightweight Pro Cushion midsole construction provides high shock absorption around the forefoot and the heel. Pro Cushion guarantees superior comfort and long-lasting functionality. The breathable and anti-microbial OrthoLite® insole is anatomically shaped and pre-moulded; it ensures great fit as well as perfect moisture management and an odourless and bacteria-free foot climate. The Pro Bridge arch support offers additional torsional rigidity in the midfoot area, without compromising the structural integrity of the shoe. And whatever the conditions are, the Dura GRIP outsole guarantees good traction for a safe run.

column4: Road Running Shoe Elexir III Velcro/Lace Junior
column9: The Elexir III Jr, is offered in two versions: One with classic elastic lacing, and one with quick and easy Velcro closure. The comfortable and solid running shoe for boys and girls is equipped with an anatomically shaped and pre-moulded I-Shape insole for stability and fit, a Cushion Fit midsole construction shock absorption, a very lightweight but durable Cushion Fit midsole, and a moulded Control Bridge arch support around the midfoot. The Dura Grip outsole ensures grip and added durability on many surfaces; a special impact zone deflects impact, setting the foot up for a smooth transition.

The comfortable and solid running shoe for boys and girls is equipped with an anatomically shaped and pre-moulded I-Shape insole for stability and fit, a Cushion Fit midsole construction shock absorption, a very lightweight but durable Cushion Fit midsole, and a moulded Control Bridge arch support around the midfoot. The Dura Grip outsole ensures grip and added durability on many surfaces; a special impact zone deflects impact, setting the foot up for a smooth transition.

column4: Road Running Shoe Tokyo Stability II Men
column9: With the Tokyo Stability II for men, PRO TOUCH offers a stable and solid running shoe with great comfort and flex. The breathable shoe is designed for runners with a normal arch, providing a comfortable ride mile after. The innovative and lightweight Pro Cushion midsole construction provides high shock absorption around the forefoot and the heel. Pro Cushion guarantees superior comfort and long-lasting functionality. The breathable and anti-microbial OrthoLite® insole is anatomically shaped and pre-moulded; it ensures great fit as well as perfect moisture management and an odourless and bacteria-free foot climate. The Pro Bridge arch support offers additional torsional rigidity in the midfoot area, without compromising the structural integrity of the shoe. And whatever the conditions are, the Dura GRIP outsole guarantees good traction for a safe run.

The Speed Rebel is a high-performance indoor handball shoe that combines minimum weight with excellent comfort and support. To stabilize the foot during extreme lateral movements and quick directional changes, the Speed Rebel is equipped with Stability Wings. In addition the Pro Wrap technology  further re-enforces the shoe and gives the foot for enhanced motion control and stability. The upper consists of tough PU and a lightweight technical mesh to ensure high breathability  and comfort. The pre-shaped OrthoLite® insole is highly breathable, long lasting and anti-microbial. In combination with the lightweight midsole compound, it provides superior cushioning and durability. The ProBridge is a lightweight arch support that provides additional torsional rigidity in the midfoot while retaining the structural integrity of the shoe. The non-marking Pro Grip outsole has premium grip characteristics and a high abrasion resistance.

The non-marking Easy Grip rubber outsole is durable and offers grip for all your indoor activities.

The Velcro version of the Rebel Jr was specifically developed for young athletes looking for a lightweight, stable and comfortable performance shoe. A breathable lightweight upper mesh in conjunction with the PRO TOUCH Wrap technology provides the foot with enhanced motion control and fit. The Control Bridge midfoot support and a lightweight midsole compound enhance shock absorption and stability. In addition the Rebel is equipped with anatomically shaped and pre-moulded EVA I-Shape insoles for improved comfort. To protect the upper from excessive wear the toe area is re-enforced with an abrasion resistant PU material. The non-marking Dura Grip outsole offers good grip and reliable durability for a multitude of different indoor sports.

The fabric of the PRO TOUCH Iris tight for women is very elastic, breathable, and equipped with DRY PLUS moisture, a fibre technology that rapidly transports moisture away from the body to keep you dry and comfortable. Strategically placed 360-degree reflective elements improve your safety when you run in low light conditions.

Keys or other important small objects can be securely kept in the integrated pocket.

If you need a little more protection from the weather but not the warmth of a full running jacket, the PRO TOUCH Aaron sleeveless jacket is a great piece of equipment. In addition, the woven fabric features DRY PLUS moisture, an integrated fibre technology that rapidly transports moisture away from the body. Strategically placed 360-degree reflective elements improve your safety when you run in low light conditions. The Aaron Vest has storage pockets on the sides.

The Rebel Jr was specifically developed for young athletes looking for a lightweight, stable and comfortable performance shoe. A breathable lightweight upper mesh in conjunction with the PRO TOUCH Wrap technology provides the foot with enhanced motion control and fit. In addition the Rebel is equipped with anatomically shaped and pre-moulded EVA I-Shape insoles for improved comfort. To protect the upper from excessive wear the toe area is re-enforced with an abrasion resistant PU material. The Speed Rebel is a high-performance indoor handball shoe that combines minimum weight with excellent comfort and support. To stabilize the foot during extreme lateral movements and quick directional changes, the Speed Rebel is equipped with Stability Wings. In addition the Pro Wrap technology  further re-enforces the shoe and gives the foot for enhanced motion control and stability. The upper consists of tough PU and a lightweight technical mesh to ensure high breathability  and comfort. The pre-shaped OrthoLite® insole is highly breathable, long lasting and anti-microbial. In combination with the lightweight midsole compound, it provides superior cushioning and durability. The ProBridge is a lightweight arch support that provides additional torsional rigidity in the midfoot while retaining the structural integrity of the shoe. The non-marking Pro Grip outsole has premium grip characteristics and a high abrasion resistance.

column4: Road Running Shoe Chicago Stability II Men
column9: The Chicago Stability for men is a solid and breathable running shoe. The shoe features a pre-moulded I-Shape insole for superior stability and fit. The Cushion Fit midsole construction of the Chicago Stability is designed to reliably absorb shock and provide high comfort. The weight of the Cushion Fit midsole is reduced to the minimum, without compromising its durability. Whilst reducing the overall weight of the shoe, positioning a Control Bridge moulded arch support around the midfoot area also enhanced the overall stability. The advanced Dura Grip outsole material provides enhanced grip and added durability for road running.  Available in colors: Blue/green/black and white/black/gold/blue

column4: Road Running Shoe Chicago Stability II Women
column9: The women’s version of the Chicago Stability running shoe was adapted to women’s specific needs. It’s a comfortable and breathable running shoe for beginners to intermediate runners, offering plenty of guidance for a neutral gait. The shoe features an anatomically shaped and pre-moulded I-Shape insole for superior stability and fit. The Cushion Fit midsole construction of the Chicago Stability is designed to reliably absorb shock and provide high comfort. The weight of the Cushion Fit midsole is reduced to the minimum, without compromising its durability. Whilst reducing the overall weight of the shoe, the stability was improved by integrating a Control Bridge moulded arch support around the midfoot area. The advanced Dura Grip outsole material provides enhanced grip and added durability for road running. Available in colors: White/grey/light blue and pruple/violet/white

Great comfort and low weight: The OZ Pro for men is a well-cushioned running shoe for neutral-gait runners who are looking for lightweight footwear for longer distances. The design of the shoe is sleek and reduced, but it’s not compromising any of its important performance properties: It features Cushion Fit, which is a midsole construction designed to absorb shock and provide high comfort at a very low weight. The Easy Grip outsole is very abrasion-resistant and offers good and reliable grip. On the inside, a breathable OrthoLite® insole ensures great fit as well as perfect moisture management and an odourless and bacteria-free foot climate. Available in colors: Black/white/red, blue/green/white, blue/orange/black and white/black/blue

The new OZ Pro for women may look reduced, sleek and modern, but it is one of PRO TOUCH’s best-cushioned running shoes for neutral-gait runners. The shoe features Cushion Fit, which is a midsole construction designed to reliably absorb shock and provide high comfort at a very low weight. Many other components of the shoe like the upper and parts of the sole construction were also redesigned to be lighter than in any other PRO TOUCH running shoe. The Easy Grip outsole is very abrasion-resistant and offers good and reliable grip. On the inside of the OZ Pro W, a breathable OrthoLite® insole ensures great fit as well as perfect moisture management and an odourless and bacteria-free foot climate.  Available in colors: Blue/dark pink/white, Purple/light violet/white and balck/pink

column9: This lightweight men’s running shoe is designed for serious, underpronating to neutral runners who work out or compete on a regular basis, preferably on hard surfaces like tarmac, gravel, or solid soil. A breathable lightweight upper mesh in conjunction with the PRO TOUCH Wrap technology provides the foot with enhanced motion control and fit. The Speed Rebel is a high-performance indoor handball shoe that combines minimum weight with excellent comfort and support. To stabilize the foot during extreme lateral movements and quick directional changes, the Speed Rebel is equipped with Stability Wings. In addition the Pro Wrap technology  further re-enforces the shoe and gives the foot for enhanced motion control and stability. The upper consists of tough PU and a lightweight technical mesh to ensure high breathability  and comfort. The pre-shaped OrthoLite® insole is highly breathable, long lasting and anti-microbial. In combination with the lightweight midsole compound, it provides superior cushioning and durability. The ProBridge is a lightweight arch support that provides additional torsional rigidity in the midfoot while retaining the structural integrity of the shoe. The non-marking Pro Grip outsole has premium grip characteristics and a high abrasion resistance.

The Speed Rebel is a high-performance indoor handball shoe that combines minimum weight with excellent comfort and support. To stabilize the foot during extreme lateral movements and quick directional changes, the Speed Rebel is equipped with Stability Wings. In addition the Pro Wrap technology  further re-enforces the shoe and gives the foot for enhanced motion control and stability. The upper consists of tough PU and a lightweight technical mesh to ensure high breathability  and comfort. The pre-shaped OrthoLite® insole is highly breathable, long lasting and anti-microbial. In combination with the lightweight midsole compound, it provides superior cushioning and durability. The ProBridge is a lightweight arch support that provides additional torsional rigidity in the midfoot while retaining the structural integrity of the shoe. The non-marking Pro Grip outsole has premium grip characteristics and a high abrasion resistance.

The Speed Rebel is a high-performance indoor handball shoe that combines minimum weight with excellent comfort and support. To stabilize the foot during extreme lateral movements and quick directional changes, the Speed Rebel is equipped with Stability Wings. In addition the Pro Wrap technology  further re-enforces the shoe and gives the foot for enhanced motion control and stability. The upper consists of tough PU and a lightweight technical mesh to ensure high breathability  and comfort. The pre-shaped OrthoLite® insole is highly breathable, long lasting and anti-microbial. In combination with the lightweight midsole compound, it provides superior cushioning and durability. The ProBridge is a lightweight arch support that provides additional torsional rigidity in the midfoot while retaining the structural integrity of the shoe. The non-marking Pro Grip outsole has premium grip characteristics and a high abrasion resistance.

The Curtney is our women-specific 3in1 jacket with AQUAMAX® 5.5 weatherproof coating. Designed to go anywhere with you on hikes, treks, travel or city, it can do it all: It's waterproof, features stretch for a great fit and freedom of movement, a detachable hood, and pre-formed elbows. Additional features for great protection from the elements and great comfort include bottom adjustment, waterproof zips, a chin guard, fully taped seams, and adjustable cuffs. With the M.Z.S zip-in system, it’s easy to adjust the insulation of the Curtney to the weather: wear the outer shell with the liner on cold days, unzip the liner whenever you need rain or snow protection but less insulation, or wear the liner separately as a warm outer layer when it’s dry. Material: 100% Polyester Performance: 2-layer laminate Water Column: 5,000mm Features: zip-off hood, pre-formed elbows, bottom adjustment, waterproof zippers, chin guard, adjustable cuffs, fully taped seams Technology: AQUAMAX 5.5, M.Z.S. (McKinley Zip-In System), YKK zippers, Stretch

The entire jacket, including a storm hood, packs into an internal pocket, so you can bring it along anywhere, anytime. column4: Sequence AQX M, McKinely, Active Outdoor
column9: Sequence AQX M   The Sequence AQX is a waterproof, well cushioned, and lightweight outdoor boot designed to offer maximum performance, comfort, and breathability. Although it is made of the lightest materials available, it offers enough support for serious trekking and hiking. The anatomical shape of the collar enhances the freedom of movement while supporting and protecting the Achilles area. The overall construction of the boot is based on McKINLEY’s new Butterfly footwear technology, featuring the new Butterfly Shank and the Butterfly Lacing Support. The Butterfly Shank is a thermoplastic urethane link in the outsole between the heel and the forefoot that allows a smooth and stable impact when the foot hits the ground. It also provides torsional stability and strength to the midfoot, thus supporting an easy toe-off. The new Butterfly Lacing Support is a „wrap-around“ lacing design that links the classic metal-hook lacing to the boot’s upper for a more individual adjustment. In addition to the Butterfly Technology features, the Sequence AQX is equipped with McKINLEY’s waterproof AQUAMAX ® technology, making this extremely versatile lightweight boot super reliable in all conditions. Material: Synthetic & Mesh Liner: Synthetic Outsole: Rubber (STICO 3) Midsole: molded EVA (high cut) Weight: 530 g Special: AQUAMAX®, Ortholite®, Performance Fit, Butterf ly Shank, Butterf ly Lacing Support, Deep Pull Hook, Metal Hook, Rubber Toe Protector, Comfort Cushion System

The overall construction of the boot is based on McKINLEY’s new Butterfly footwear technology, featuring the new Butterfly Shank and the Butterfly Lacing Support. The Butterfly Shank is a thermoplastic urethane link in the outsole between the heel and the forefoot that allows a smooth and stable impact when the foot hits the ground. It also provides torsional stability and strength to the midfoot, thus supporting an easy toe-off. The new Butterfly Lacing Support is a „wrap-around“ lacing design that links the classic metal-hook lacing to the boot’s upper for a more individual adjustment. In addition to the Butterfly Technology features, the Sequence AQX is equipped with McKINLEY’s waterproof AQUAMAX ® technology, making this extremely versatile lightweight boot super reliable in all conditions. column4: Trekker CL, Footwear, McKinley, Mountain Tec
column9: Trekker CL   McKINLEY’s Trekker CL is a classic full-leather trekking and hiking boot designed for real outdoor adventures. The lasted construction with leather lining and collar guarantees ultimate comfort and an unbeatable feeling inside the boot. The stability and durability needed for extended, technical trekking is provided by the high-quality leather upper and the robust, traditional lacing system with metal hooks and a deep pull hook at the ankles. A rubber toe cup and a heel cup protect the foot against impact and offer additional stability. column9: Cisco Comfort W   Very well equipped multi-functional shoe for a variety of outdoor activities, travel or everyday use. This version of McKINLEY’s Cisco was designed to deliver the utmost comfort possible for long and strenuous days out on the road or in the mountains. This was the challenge that the McKinley footwear designers had to face, and they came up with lightweight and durable materials, Ortholite insoles (one of the leading insoles for comfort and fit) and a Contragrip® outsole featuring a unique combination of a special rubber compound, tread geometry, and density for effortless walking or hiking with optimal grip. column4: Sequence AQX W, McKinely, Active Outdoor
column9: Sequence AQX W   The Sequence AQX is a waterproof, well cushioned, and lightweight outdoor boot designed to offer maximum performance, comfort, and breathability. Although it is made of the lightest materials available, it offers enough support for serious trekking and hiking. The anatomical shape of the collar enhances the freedom of movement while supporting and protecting the Achilles area. The overall construction of the boot is based on McKINLEY’s new Butterfly footwear technology, featuring the new Butterfly Shank and the Butterfly Lacing Support. The Butterfly Shank is a thermoplastic urethane link in the outsole between the heel and the forefoot that allows a smooth and stable impact when the foot hits the ground. It also provides torsional stability and strength to the midfoot, thus supporting an easy toe-off. The new Butterfly Lacing Support is a „wrap-around“ lacing design that links the classic metal-hook lacing to the boot’s upper for a more individual adjustment. In addition to the Butterfly Technology features, the Sequence AQX is equipped with McKINLEY’s waterproof AQUAMAX ® technology, making this extremely versatile lightweight boot super reliable in all conditions. A fully seamsealed flysheet provides maximum protection, while all stress points are additionally reinforced for extra durability. The inner tents are zip divided, with the Vario Vent System allowing great air exchange through all parts of the Kos 4. Once taken out of its oversized carrying bag, the Kos 4 is quickly set up thanks to the easy colour coding. The poles are made of extra strong fibreglass. Adding to the overall comfort of the extremely versatile Kos 4 are a lamp holder and luminous guylines.

For active women, the Baxter is a perfect 3in1 jacket consisting of a functional, weatherproof shell jacket and an extra insulating zip-in fleece for colder days. Whether you like to hike, trek, or snowshoe, the waterproof and breathable AQUAMAX® 8.8 membrane of the 2-layer outer jacket and the Airflow ventilation will greatly contribute to the management of your body temperature while protecting you from the elements. With a zip-off hood, pre-formed elbows, bottom adjustment and chin guard, fully taped seams, adjustable cuffs, and brushed tricot at the neck, the Baxter women’s 3in1 is equipped with everything necessary for best comfort and performance. Strategically placed stretch inserts provide the necessary freedom of movement. The zip-in fleece jacket also features Stretchfleece inserts where necessary to perfectly harmonize with the outer shell. The HELIUM 100 is the most versatile and most powerful headlamp McKINLEY ever offered. This puristically designed model is equipped with one high-output Boost 1 W LED with Optic Lens and four improved high performance LEDs, which produce a 70-meter beam of light with up to 100 lumen. It also features a little Red Single Power LED for uncompromising night vision. The compact, super-bright HELIUM 100 simply serves all lighting needs. The casing is protected against high humidity, snow, rain, or quick immersion of water according to the IPX4 standard. The economic mode optimizes the battery lifetime and offers an extended burn time of up to 60 hours. The customisable polyester elastic headstrap is available in different colours. It’s a fun and unique way to personalize your headlamp. For less weight or more lighting performance in cold temperatures, the HELIUM 100 can be operated with lithium batteries.   Features: CE approved operated with three AAA batteries easy-open battery case flashing mode adjustable headstrap comfortable to wear compatible with lithium batteries

column4: Killay Hardshell Jacket wms, Mountain tec, McKinley
column9: Killay Hardshell Jacket wms The women’s Killay hardshell is the perfect emergency jacket that fits in the smallest backpack: It’s super lightweight, packs extremely small in a separate bag, has a storm hood, and comes with fully taped seams and the waterproof and breathable AQUAMAX® 10.10 membrane. Whether it’s wind or water, this 2-layer hardshell will protect you from cooling down or getting soaked. The jacket has elastic hems that close tightly around wrists and hip to reduce the overall weight of the jacket and to provide a close and feminine fit. The Killay even has a chest pocket to fit its own compression bag or any other small item. It needs minimal space, so make sure to take the Killay everywhere you go! Material: 100% Polyamide Technology: 2-layer laminate Water Column: 10,000mm Breathability: 10,000g/m2/24h Features: storm hood, separate packing bag, waterproof zips, chin guard, fully taped seams, YKK zippers Technology: AQUAMAX® 10.10, 89.95 €

column4: Mountain Tec, Short-sleeve T-Shirt, Aela Women
column9: McKINLEY’s Mountain-Tec Aela short-sleeve T-shirt for women with appealing all-over print is designed for mountain and high-impact sports like speed hiking or trail running. The moisture wicking and antibacterial properties due to DRY PLUS moisture and Polygiene® help regulate your body climate, keep your skin dry, and avoid unwanted body odours. The shirt also features an integrated UV shield rated UPF 30. The Alea’s stretch fabric guarantees unrestricted freedom of movement, while the flatlock seams avoid chafing when you are hiking, trekking, or working out. column4: Lanila Padded Jacket ux, Mountain tec, McKinley
column9: Lanila 60 ux If you need extra warmth on your trekking expedition or hiking trip without a bulky feel and excessive weight, the Lanila padded jacket with PrimaLoft® insulation is probably one of the most functional jackets you can bring. The Lanila can be worn as an insulating mid layer or as an outer layer. A durable water repellent finish makes sure that you don’t get soaked. And even if the PrimaLoft® padding should ever get moist or wet, it won’t loose any of its insulating properties. In addition, the PrimaLoft® fibres are inside a wind-breaking, high-density Polyamide fabric that blocks the wind to keep you warm. Two front pockets and one external chest pocket offer plenty of space for all your valuables, and the elastic binding cuffs guarantee a comfortable and tight fit. The entire jacket, including its storm hood, packs into its own internal pocket, so you can always bring it along. column4: Northfield Pants men, Mountain tec, McKinley
column9: Northfield Pants men The perfect pant for rock climbers needs to be abrasion resistant, yet stretchy enough to guarantee that none of their moves are restricted. McKINLEY’s Mountain-Tec Northfield pant fulfills both requirements: reinforced areas like the inner leg bottoms, the knees and the seat for additional abrasion resistance, as well as a double-weave robust stretch fabric for full freedom of movement. The fabric of the Northfield pant is equipped with DRY PLUS moisture and boasts a durable water repellent finish and is thus wind and water resistant, breathable, moisture wicking, and fast-drying. The bottom hem is elastic and adjustable. To avoid that you get lost on your way to the top, the thigh pocket is large enough to fit a map. Material: 90% Polyester, 10% Elastane Features: pre-formed knees, integrated belt, reinforced fabric at hem, YKK zipper Technology: DRY PLUS moisture, Stretch 79.95 €

Tretford Hardshell Jacket wms Minimum weight and a small pack size are key to successful multi-day expeditions or hut-to-hut hikes. The Tretford hardshell for women is a wind- and waterproof 2.5-layer jacket with AQUAMAX® 10.10 membrane that is extremely lightweight and packs down to a very small size. Additional functional features of this great outdoor jacket include a fully adjustable hood, adjustable hem and sleeves, two large front pockets, and a very efficient ventilation system. column4: Midway T-Shirt wms, Mountain tec, McKinley

column4: Malon Softshell Jacket wms, McKinley, Mountain tec
column9: Malon Softshell Jacket wms The women’s Malon softshell is made with a double weave fabric that is breathable, wind resistant, and stretchy for pleasant and comfortable outdoor experiences in dry and breezy climates. The jacket is also appreciated by boulderers and rock climbers, because the stretch fabric offers great freedom of movement and the Polyamid fabric provides abrasion resistant properties. Material: 90% Polyamide, 10% Elastane Features: storm hood, chin guard, hem adjustment system, pre-formed elbows, YKK zippers Technology: DRY PLUS moisture, Stretch 69.95 €

column4: Lanila Padded Jacket ux, Mountain tec, McKinley
column9: Lanila 60 ux If you need extra warmth on your trekking expedition or hiking trip without a bulky feel and excessive weight, the Lanila padded jacket with PrimaLoft® insulation is probably one of the most functional jackets you can bring. The Lanila can be worn as an insulating mid layer or as an outer layer. A durable water repellent finish makes sure that you don’t get soaked. And even if the PrimaLoft® padding should ever get moist or wet, it won’t loose any of its insulating properties. In addition, the PrimaLoft® fibres are inside a wind-breaking, high-density Polyamide fabric that blocks the wind to keep you warm. Two front pockets and one external chest pocket offer plenty of space for all your valuables, and the elastic binding cuffs guarantee a comfortable and tight fit. The entire jacket, including its storm hood, packs into its own internal pocket, so you can always bring it along. Material: 100% Polyamide, PrimaLoft® 60 Padding Features: storm hood, chin guard, hood adjustment system, hem adjustment system, pre-formed elbows, YKK zippers Technology: PrimaLoft® 89.95 €

column4: Millen Light Hardshell Jacket wms, Mountain tec, McKinley
column9: Millen Light Hardshell Jacket wms The Millen Light hardshell jacket for women was designed for the most demanding alpinists. The three-layer jacket features the effective Airflow ventilation system and the high-performance AQUAMAX® 20.20 membrane, which allows the fabric of the Millen Light to transport moisture away from the skin. At the same time, the fabric is reliably wind- and waterproof. A storm hood with visor for additional rain protection, fully taped seams, and waterproof zippers support this function. The jacket’s stretch fabric offers unrestricted freedom of movement. The two front pockets are positioned higher than usual for easy access when a backpack is carried. Sleeves, hem, cuffs, and storm hood can be individually adjusted for perfect fit and protection. column4: McKINLEY active outdoor camping tent kreta 5
column9: The Kreta 5 is McKINLEY’s robust and extra large tunnel tent for one entire family. This tent offers adult standing height (max. 1.90cm) and enough room for five people. For ultimate comfort, the Kreta 5 consists of three parts: two berths for sleeping (one for three and one for two persons) and a large living chamber with large panorama windows and side doors, all with mesh for mosquito- free ventilation and a fully integrated, sewn-in PE floor. The inner tents are zip divided. The third part is a small wind-protected outside porch with an additional tent entrance. A fully seam-sealed flysheet provides maximum protection. All stress point are reinforced for guaranteed durability. The Vario Vent System provides great air exchange through all parts of the Kreta 5. The colour coding helps with the pitching of the tent, which comes complete with an oversized carrying bag. Adding to the overall comfort of the Kreta 5 are a lamp holder and luminous guylines.

Geodesic dome tent with great wind stability due to multiply crossed poles. With two entrances and vestibules, the Sherpa 3 offers enough space for up to three persons and their luggage. column4: Sequence AQX W, McKinely, Active Outdoor
column9: Sequence AQX W   The Sequence AQX is a waterproof, well cushioned, and lightweight outdoor boot designed to offer maximum performance, comfort, and breathability. Although it is made of the lightest materials available, it offers enough support for serious trekking and hiking. The anatomical shape of the collar enhances the freedom of movement while supporting and protecting the Achilles area. The overall construction of the boot is based on McKINLEY’s new Butterfly footwear technology, featuring the new Butterfly Shank and the Butterfly Lacing Support. The Butterfly Shank is a thermoplastic urethane link in the outsole between the heel and the forefoot that allows a smooth and stable impact when the foot hits the ground. It also provides torsional stability and strength to the midfoot, thus supporting an easy toe-off. The new Butterfly Lacing Support is a „wrap-around“ lacing design that links the classic metal-hook lacing to the boot’s upper for a more individual adjustment. In addition to the Butterfly Technology features, the Sequence AQX is equipped with McKINLEY’s waterproof AQUAMAX ® technology, making this extremely versatile lightweight boot super reliable in all conditions. Material: Synthetic & Mesh Liner: Synthetic Outsole: Rubber (STICO 3) Midsole: molded EVA (high cut) Weight: 450 g Special: AQUAMAX®, Ortholite®, Performance Fit, Butterf ly Shank, Butterf ly Lacing Support, Deep Pull Hook, Metal Hook, Rubber Toe Protector, Comfort Cushion System

column4: Magma AQX W, McKinley, Mountain Tec
column9: Magma AQX W   The Magma AQX is one of McKINLEY’s Active Outdoor trekking and hiking boots that is designed for maximum performance with minimum weight. It’s a great choice for outdoor enthusiasts looking for a versatile trekking boot at a highly competitive price. With an upper made of leather and synthetic, the Magma AQX is also equipped with McKINLEY’s waterproof AQUAMAX® technology, making this all-rounder reliable in all conditions. In addition, the VIBRAM® outsole provides tremendous grip in any kind of weather and terrain. Its durable compound ensures extended life and extremely high friction on all surfaces. For ideal fit, the Magma AQX features a classic lacing system that runs through durable metal hooks with an additional deep pull hook and Butterfly support that links the lacing directly to the upper for a more individual adjustment. column4: Sequence AQX W, McKinely, Active Outdoor
column9: Sequence AQX W   The Sequence AQX is a waterproof, well cushioned, and lightweight outdoor boot designed to offer maximum performance, comfort, and breathability. Although it is made of the lightest materials available, it offers enough support for serious trekking and hiking. The anatomical shape of the collar enhances the freedom of movement while supporting and protecting the Achilles area. The overall construction of the boot is based on McKINLEY’s new Butterfly footwear technology, featuring the new Butterfly Shank and the Butterfly Lacing Support. The Butterfly Shank is a thermoplastic urethane link in the outsole between the heel and the forefoot that allows a smooth and stable impact when the foot hits the ground. It also provides torsional stability and strength to the midfoot, thus supporting an easy toe-off. The new Butterfly Lacing Support is a „wrap-around“ lacing design that links the classic metal-hook lacing to the boot’s upper for a more individual adjustment. In addition to the Butterfly Technology features, the Sequence AQX is equipped with McKINLEY’s waterproof AQUAMAX ® technology, making this extremely versatile lightweight boot super reliable in all conditions. column4: Sequence AQX W, McKinely, Active Outdoor
column9: Sequence AQX W   The Sequence AQX is a waterproof, well cushioned, and lightweight outdoor boot designed to offer maximum performance, comfort, and breathability. Although it is made of the lightest materials available, it offers enough support for serious trekking and hiking. The anatomical shape of the collar enhances the freedom of movement while supporting and protecting the Achilles area. The overall construction of the boot is based on McKINLEY’s new Butterfly footwear technology, featuring the new Butterfly Shank and the Butterfly Lacing Support. The Butterfly Shank is a thermoplastic urethane link in the outsole between the heel and the forefoot that allows a smooth and stable impact when the foot hits the ground. It also provides torsional stability and strength to the midfoot, thus supporting an easy toe-off. The new Butterfly Lacing Support is a „wrap-around“ lacing design that links the classic metal-hook lacing to the boot’s upper for a more individual adjustment. In addition to the Butterfly Technology features, the Sequence AQX is equipped with McKINLEY’s waterproof AQUAMAX ® technology, making this extremely versatile lightweight boot super reliable in all conditions. Material: Synthetic & Mesh Liner: Synthetic Outsole: Rubber (STICO 3) Midsole: molded EVA (high cut) Weight: 450 g Special: AQUAMAX®, Ortholite®, Performance Fit, Butterf ly Shank, Butterf ly Lacing Support, Deep Pull Hook, Metal Hook, Rubber Toe Protector, Comfort Cushion System

column4: Basalt AQX M, McKinley, Mountain Tec
column9: Basalt AQX M   McKINLEY’s Basalt AQX is a great mid-cut trekking boot ideal for a multitude of outdoor activities. It resembles the perfect combination of weight, stability, weather protection and allterrain capability. The comfortable boot is equipped with waterproof and breathable AQUAMAX® technology to keep the feet dry and well conditioned at any time. The mid-cut design is perfect for the right amount of stability and protection around the ankles, yet not restricting the flexibility of the foot for quick and nimble hiking. The reliable McKINLEY Trekking outsole offers great grip and stability in any terrain. For additional comfort and stability, the Basalt features protectors on both heels and toe. The lacing with Butterfly Lacing Support and additional deep pull hook provides perfect fit. The Basalt AQX is a true performer for any weather and outdoor adventure! Material: Suede Leather/Synthetic Liner: Synthetic Outsole: McKINLEY Trekking Midsole: PU/rubber Weight: 385g (size 42) Special: AQUAMAX® Elite, Confort Fit, Butterf ly Lacing Support, Deep Pull Hook, Metal hook, Easy Entrance Loop, Rubber Toe Protector, Heel Protector

It’s a great choice for outdoor enthusiasts looking for a versatile trekking boot at a highly competitive price. With an upper made of leather and synthetic, the Magma AQX is also equipped with McKINLEY’s waterproof AQUAMAX® technology, making this all-rounder reliable in all conditions. In addition, the VIBRAM® outsole provides tremendous grip in any kind of weather and terrain. Its durable compound ensures extended life and extremely high friction on all surfaces. For ideal fit, the Magma AQX features a classic lacing system that runs through durable metal hooks with an additional deep pull hook and Butterfly support that links the lacing directly to the upper for a more individual adjustment. Material: Leather/Synthetic / Textile Liner: Synthetic Outsole: Vibram® (STICO 2) Midsole: PU Weight: 590 g Special: AQUAMAX®, Comfort Fit, Butterf ly Lacing Support, Deep Pull Hook, Metal Hook, Heel Protector, Rubber Toe Protector

column4: Osorno AQX W, McKinley, X function
column9: Osorno AQX W   The Osorno AQX W is a durable and waterproof trail shoe for active women who enjoy a good trail run or speed hike. This high-performance shoe is equipped with AQUAMAX® Elite, a reliable Vibram® outsole and a flexible and shock absorbing midsole for extra comfort and control. The mesh liner helps regulate the foot climate, the waterproof AQUAMAX® technology ensures additional breathability. The Fast Lace System of the Osorno AQX W easily allows you to re-adjust your shoes at any time; a protective flap covers the closure element of the system and the excess lace, avoiding them to get caught in branches and keeping dirt out. Material: Synthetic Liner: Synthetic Outsole: Vibram® Midsole: molded EVA (low cut) Weight: 315g (size 38) Special: AQUAMAX® Elite, Performance Fit, Flex Zone, Fast Lace System, Gilly Lacing, Easy Entrance Loop, Rubber Toe Protector

column4: Coddy men short, McKinley, Active Outdoor
column9: Coddy men short   The Coddy pants are our top functional Active Outdoor trekking pants, equipped with DRY PLUS and UV protection. With its many useful features, it is an essential part of your equipment: DRY PLUS and Polygiene® take care of your microclimate and keep you dry and free of odour-causing bacteria and fungi; with the bottom leg zippers, you can comfortably wear light low-cut outdoor shoes as well as hiking boots; the pre-formed knees, the partially elastic waist and the integrated belt ensure perfect fit. Last but not least: The zip-off function converts the Coddy into functional outdoor shorts for hot summer days. Great garment for travelling. Also available in special sizes for longer or shorter legs.   Material: 100% Nylon   Features: pre-formed knees, partial elastic waist, bottom-zip opening, integrated belt, zip-off pants   Technology: DRY PLUS moisture, sun protection UPF 50, Polygiene®

Chromosome M   The Chromosome is a very athletic, well-cushioned and highly breathable trail shoe for ambitious speed hikers, trail runners but it´s also great for everyday use. The construction of the shoe is based on McKINLEY’s new BUTTERFLY footwear technology. Being part of the X-Function collection, the lightest materials were used to offer the best functionality for active outdoor athletes. The lightweight upper of the Chromosome offers maximum performance and air permeability. The special Butterfly Lacing Support allows you to individually adjust the fit by applying different pressure and tightness in different strategic areas around the foot. The outsole features the new Butterfly grip zone, which delivers reliable grip even in uneven or rougher terrain. The Chromosome is designed to perform! Material: Synthetic & Mesh Liner: Synthetic Outsole: Rubber Midsole: molded EVA (low cut) Weight: 350 g Special: Ortholite®, Performance Fit, Butterf ly Grip Zone, Butterf ly Lacing Support, Flex Zone, Fast Lace System, Rubber Toe Protector

column4: McKINLEY family tent active outdoor camping Samos 6
column9: The Samos 6 is the largest McKINLEY family tent with two opposite berths to guarantee maximum privacy between parents and their children. This spacious tent is easy to set up and designed for longer camping holidays and heavyduty usage: All potential stress points received reinforcement patches for extra durability and the tent has an additional PE floor. The fully seamsealed flysheet guarantees maximum weather protection. The large inside area with all its chambers is always well ventilated by the Vario Vent System. Adding to the overall comfort of the Samos 6 are a lamp holder and luminous guylines.

column4: McKINLEY family tent active outdoor alpha 5
column9: Easy setup family tent designed for weekends or longer camping holidays. Due to the two adjacent but separated berths for sleeping, the awning of the Alpha 5 offers a very spacious interior with an additional PE floor and Vario Vent System for perfect airflow and ventilation inside. With reinforced potential stress points and a fully seam-sealed flysheet for maximum protection, the tent is well prepared for heavy-duty use in all weather conditions. Additional features are a lamp holder as well as luminous guylines for extra safety at night.

column4: McKINLEY family tent active outdoor camping ventura 5
column9: This family tent for five persons with classic dome shape offers a lot of headroom, one berth for sleeping and a large awning with plenty of space and comfort for the entire family. With the Vario Vent System, the interior of the McKINLEY Ventura 5 stays well ventilated and condensation-free. Reinforcement patches on all potential stress points ensure longevity of the Ventura 5. A fully seam-sealed flysheet guarantees maximum weather protection. The tent offers easy setup, a lamp holder, and luminous guylines for extra safety around the tent at night.

column4: Trekker CL, Footwear, McKinley, Mountain Tec
column9: Trekker CL   McKINLEY’s Trekker CL is a classic full-leather trekking and hiking boot designed for real outdoor adventures. The lasted construction with leather lining and collar guarantees ultimate comfort and an unbeatable feeling inside the boot. The stability and durability needed for extended, technical trekking is provided by the high-quality leather upper and the robust, traditional lacing system with metal hooks and a deep pull hook at the ankles. A rubber toe cup and a heel cup protect the foot against impact and offer additional stability. Material: Full Leather, oiled Liner: Leather Outsole: Vibram® (STICO 3) Midsole: PU Construction: Lasted Weight: 860 g Special: Comfort Fit, Deep Pull Hook, Metal Hook, Heel Protector, Rubber Toe Protector

column4: Cisco Comfort W, McKinley, Active Outdoor
column9: Cisco Comfort W   Very well equipped multi-functional shoe for a variety of outdoor activities, travel or everyday use. This version of McKINLEY’s Cisco was designed to deliver the utmost comfort possible for long and strenuous days out on the road or in the mountains. This was the challenge that the McKinley footwear designers had to face, and they came up with lightweight and durable materials, Ortholite insoles (one of the leading insoles for comfort and fit) and a Contragrip® outsole featuring a unique combination of a special rubber compound, tread geometry, and density for effortless walking or hiking with optimal grip. The liner of this boot is equipped with McKINLEY’s waterproof AQUAMAX® technology. Material: Suede Leather/Synthetic & Mesh Liner: Synthetic Outsole: McKINLEY Hiking Contragrip Rubber (STICO 2) Midsole: molded EVA (high cut) Weight: 415 g Special: AQUAMAX®, Ortholite®, Performance Fit, Metal Hook, Easy Entry Loop, Heel Protector, Rubber Toe Protector, Comfort Cushion System

column4: Sequence AQX M, McKinely, Active Outdoor
column9: Sequence AQX M   The Sequence AQX is a waterproof, well cushioned, and lightweight outdoor boot designed to offer maximum performance, comfort, and breathability. Although it is made of the lightest materials available, it offers enough support for serious trekking and hiking. The anatomical shape of the collar enhances the freedom of movement while supporting and protecting the Achilles area. The overall construction of the boot is based on McKINLEY’s new Butterfly footwear technology, featuring the new Butterfly Shank and the Butterfly Lacing Support. The Butterfly Shank is a thermoplastic urethane link in the outsole between the heel and the forefoot that allows a smooth and stable impact when the foot hits the ground. It also provides torsional stability and strength to the midfoot, thus supporting an easy toe-off. The new Butterfly Lacing Support is a „wrap-around“ lacing design that links the classic metal-hook lacing to the boot’s upper for a more individual adjustment. In addition to the Butterfly Technology features, the Sequence AQX is equipped with McKINLEY’s waterproof AQUAMAX ® technology, making this extremely versatile lightweight boot super reliable in all conditions. Material: Synthetic & Mesh Liner: Synthetic Outsole: Rubber (STICO 3) Midsole: molded EVA (high cut) Weight: 530 g Special: AQUAMAX®, Ortholite®, Performance Fit, Butterf ly Shank, Butterf ly Lacing Support, Deep Pull Hook, Metal Hook, Rubber Toe Protector, Comfort Cushion System

The anatomical shape of the collar enhances the freedom of movement while supporting and protecting the Achilles area. The overall construction of the boot is based on McKINLEY’s new Butterfly footwear technology, featuring the new Butterfly Shank and the Butterfly Lacing Support. The Butterfly Shank is a thermoplastic urethane link in the outsole between the heel and the forefoot that allows a smooth and stable impact when the foot hits the ground. It also provides torsional stability and strength to the midfoot, thus supporting an easy toe-off. The new Butterfly Lacing Support is a „wrap-around“ lacing design that links the classic metal-hook lacing to the boot’s upper for a more individual adjustment. In addition to the Butterfly Technology features, the Sequence AQX is equipped with McKINLEY’s waterproof AQUAMAX ® technology, making this extremely versatile lightweight boot super reliable in all conditions. Material: Synthetic & Mesh Liner: Synthetic Outsole: Rubber (STICO 3) Midsole: molded EVA (high cut) Weight: 530 g Special: AQUAMAX®, Ortholite®, Performance Fit, Butterf ly Shank, Butterf ly Lacing Support, Deep Pull Hook, Metal Hook, Rubber Toe Protector, Comfort Cushion System

column4: Cisco Comfort W, McKinley, Active Outdoor
column9: Cisco Comfort W   Very well equipped multi-functional shoe for a variety of outdoor activities, travel or everyday use. This version of McKINLEY’s Cisco was designed to deliver the utmost comfort possible for long and strenuous days out on the road or in the mountains. This was the challenge that the McKinley footwear designers had to face, and they came up with lightweight and durable materials, Ortholite insoles (one of the leading insoles for comfort and fit) and a Contragrip® outsole featuring a unique combination of a special rubber compound, tread geometry, and density for effortless walking or hiking with optimal grip. The liner of this boot is equipped with McKINLEY’s waterproof AQUAMAX® technology. Material: Suede Leather/Synthetic & Mesh Liner: Synthetic Outsole: McKINLEY Hiking Contragrip Rubber (STICO 2) Midsole: molded EVA (high cut) Weight: 415 g Special: AQUAMAX®, Ortholite®, Performance Fit, Metal Hook, Easy Entry Loop, Heel Protector, Rubber Toe Protector, Comfort Cushion System

Helix M   The Helix is McKINLEY’s ultra comfortable walking shoe for everyday use, which is inspired by the rugged challenges of the Great Outdoors. The breathable and smooth suede leather upper of the Helix guarantees a balanced foot climate and a comfortable feeling inside the shoe. The outsole features McKINLEY’s new Butterf ly Grip Zone, which delivers a high level of grip even on uneven or rougher surfaces. The Gilly lacing system ensures a comfortable and snug fit. Whether you are travelling, hiking, or just walking around town, the Helix is a great and comfortable choice. column4: Yukon 50+10 W, Trekking, Mountain Tec, McKinley
column9: Yukon 50+10 W   The Yukon W is a robust and athletic women’s backpack for multiple day hikes and serious trekkings. The sophisticated and modern design includes the size adjustable ERGOFLEX Vario back panel system, a comfortable and dynamic hip belt and adjustable straps that allow the hiker to adapt the backpack to the individual torso length. In addition, the hip belt and shoulder straps of the Yukon W have a women-specific shape; the back panel is shorter to perfectly suit the female anatomy. Loads up to 20kg+ are thus evenly distributed, adding to the overall women-specific comfort and performance of this backpack. With its many features like the height adjustable top lid pocket, side access to the main compartment, a separate bottom compartment, elastic and spacious external side pockets, an integrated rain cover, hiking pole fixation, and hydration system compatibility, this backpack is a guarantee for many unforgettable adventures in the outdoors.   Material: 330D Nylon Double R/S, 600D Polyester

Yukon 45+10   The Yukon is a robust and athletic backpack for multiple day hikes and serious trekkings. The modern and sophisticated construction includes the size adjustable ERGOFLEX Vario back panel system, a comfortable and dynamic hip belt, and adjustable straps that allow the hiker to adapt the backpack to the individual torso length. Any load up to the 20kg+ capacity is thus evenly distributed, adding to the overall comfort and performance of the trekker. Katmai 40+8   Light all-season touring backpack with alpine qualities: The Katmai with 40+8 litres is ideal for weekend hikes from hut to hut. Besides its modern design, the backpack offers many great functional details such as the spacious integrated side pockets, external pockets made of elastic fabric, a height adjustable top lid, bottom compartment, ski fixation, integrated rain cover, H20 compatibility, and a trekking pole fixation. The pre-moulded ERGOFIT back plate ensures highest carrying comfort, ideal ventilation, and low weight.   Material: Nylon 210D Stripe Twill, 330D Nylon Double R/S

column4: mckinley active outdoor hiking footwear cisco men
column9: Multi-functional shoe for a variety of outdoor activities and for fast hikes in the terrain . The Cisco is a lightweight and durable low-cut shoe with CONTAGRIP outsole, featuring a unique combination of a special rubber compound, tread geometry and density. The result is what the makers of CONTAGRIP call an “Energy Ride” – almost effortless sportive hiking with optimal grip. Material: Synthetic, Mesh, EVA/Rubber, Suede Leather Outsole: CONTAGRIP® Special: Multi-grip sole
